stoneChat (a caveman peeking at modern technology) is a simple LLM Web Chat, adapted for Windows XP & IE6.

To run it, your device needs a PHP 5.4+ environment (the launcher uses PHP's built-in web server). Get it from:
https://windows.php.net/downloads/releases/archives/

On Windows XP: use php-5.4.45-Win32-VC9-x86.zip -- PHP 5.4 is the last version
to support XP and the first to include the built-in web server. PHP 5.5+ requires
Vista or later. The app code itself is written to run on any PHP 5.x.

As for all the remaining network-related problems, let the program handle them. You will also need stunnel for HTTPS:
https://www.stunnel.org/downloads.html

Download / Clone:
  Clone the repository or download the ZIP.
  Before starting, copy `CONF_SMP.INI` to `CONF.ini` and edit it to set
  your API keys, password, and providers (e.g. OpenAI, Minimax, etc.).

Install (Optional):
  Run INSTALL.cmd. It checks your environment (PHP 5.4+, stunnel, disk
  space, write permissions), copies all files to the chosen folder
  (default: C:\stoneChat), creates HISTORY\ for chat logs, and adds a
  Desktop shortcut and a Start Menu entry pointing to RUN.bat.
  (If CONF.ini is missing, the installer will automatically copy
  CONF_SMP.INI to CONF.ini for you).

To run directly:
  Double-click RUN.bat. It performs the same pre-flight checks and starts
  the local web server. If CONF.ini is missing, RUN.bat will also create
  one from the CONF_SMP.INI template.

Uninstall:
  Double-click UNINSTALL.cmd from any location (install folder or
  download folder). It reads the Desktop shortcut to find the real
  install path, stops the PHP server, removes the Desktop and Start
  Menu shortcuts, then deletes the install folder. Type YES when
  prompted to confirm. If no shortcut is found it falls back to the
  folder where UNINSTALL.cmd lives.

Then visit it in your browser. The default address is:
  http://localhost:9999

You need to edit CONF.ini according to the comments to configure the LLM and other settings -- it is very simple, just follow the comments. Placeholder values like YOUR_PASSWORD_HERE and YOUR_*_API_KEY_HERE are now rejected by the validator: replace them with real secrets before starting the server.

stoneChat is open-sourced under WTFPL at:
https://github.com/Water-Run/stoneChat
